modules.description: Provides functions to convert between hexadecimal strings and byte sequences, with support for parsing and formatting 8-bit unsigned integers. Operates on strings, bytes, and character arrays. Used to encode binary data for network transmission and decode incoming hex-encoded payloads.

Encodes and decodes characters, strings, and byte buffers into hexadecimal representations, and vice versa. Processes ASCII characters, binary strings, byte sequences, and Cstruct buffers. Converts "Mirage OS" to "4d69726167654f53" and parses hex strings back to their original binary form.
